Class IRSFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • IRSFunctions

  • public class IRSFunctions
extends java.lang.Object

    The IRSFunctions class contains methods for configuring and building the IRS's recurrent neural network (RNN)/model.

    Version:
    1.7
    Author:
    hhraulerson

    • Constructor Detail

      • IRSFunctions

        public IRSFunctions(int layerSize,
                    int miniBatchs,
                    int exSize,
                    int tbpttsize,
                    int numEpochs,
                    java.lang.String dataFilePath,
                    int numColumns)
        Default constructor for IRSFunctions class.
        Parameters:
        layerSize - number of nodes in the LSTM layer
        miniBatchs - number of miniBatchs
        exSize - the total number of examples to iterate over
        tbpttsize - the number of examples to propagate forwards and backwards through
        numEpochs - the total number of epochs (times to go through the data)
        dataFilePath - the path of the file selected by the user
        numColumns - the number of columns for the file that was uploaded/selected by the user
